            <title>[GROOVY-6621] groovy.util.Node#text incorrect when value is a NodeList</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-6621</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When groovy.util.Node#text checks for it&apos;s value being an instance of Collection, it only accounts for String children elements, which means the text() values of Node children of a NodeList value will not be part of the result.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Github PR with test case to follow.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
